ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.
M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Accuracy for all trials and sessions
Notes: 1=ADT S1 Below 85 percent Accuracy; 2=ADT S2 Below 85 percent Accuracy; 3=ADT Both S1 & S2 Below 85 percent Accuracy; 7777=Not applicable; 9999=Refuse

ElementDescription: Reaction time (milliseconds) for suicide-related word trials
Reaction time (milliseconds) for life-related word trials
Reaction time (milliseconds) for anxiety-related word trials
Reaction time (milliseconds) for depression-related word trials
Reaction time (milliseconds) for positive-valanced word trials
Reaction time (milliseconds) for positive-valanced interpersonal word trials
Accuracy for positive-valanced interpersonal word trials
Reaction time (milliseconds) for neutral-valanced word trials

Notes: MEAN suicide-related RT - MEAN neutral RT; 7777=Not applicable; 9999=Refuse
MEAN life-related RT - MEAN neutral RT; 7777=Not applicable; 9999=Refuse
MEAN anxiety-related RT - MEAN neutral RT; 7777=Not applicable; 9999=Refuse
MEAN depression-related RT - MEAN neutral RT; 7777=Not applicable; 9999=Refuse
MEAN positive-valenced RT - MEAN neutral RT; 7777=Not applicable; 9999=Refuse

ElementDescription: Interference for positive-valanced interpersonal word trials
Notes: MEAN positive-valenced interpersonal RT - MEAN neutral RT; 7777=Not applicable; 9999=Refuse
e.g., Self-Report, Parent Form, Short Form, Revised Version
